      <bioghist id="aspace_4653a43795e81cb9de96e4394f5e0acc">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Robert W. Simpson was from Brunswick, Maine. Between 1858 and 1862 he was captain and part owner of the ship Carlyle, which called at New Orleans, Liverpool, Kronstadt, and possibly other places.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_235d28aa1131bb8aa723d65c8655c1d6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Personal and business correspondence of Robert W. Simpson, ship's log, and business and financial papers concerning the voyages of the <title render="italic">
               <part>Carlyle</part>
            </title> before and during the Civil War.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_e68066f89f3b2767566b6cf8b1e83a53">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
